changes: CRITICAL FIX: Frontend now sends custom bucket headers in deployment requests
Added custom bucket headers to /api/deploy POST request
Added custom bucket headers to /api/check-versions POST request
Added custom bucket headers to /api/clear-deploy POST request
Added custom bucket headers to /api/artifacts/delete POST request
Frontend getCustomBucketHeaders() now properly used for all deployment operations
Deployment now ACTUALLY uses custom build bucket (v1.16.2 backend fix + v1.16.3 frontend fix)
Complete end-to-end custom bucket selection now fully functional
Fixed deployment failures with custom bucket selection (Backend only)
Updated s3Service.getArtifact() to accept req parameter and use dynamic buckets
Updated s3Service.getArtifactFileList() to accept req parameter
Updated deployService.deploy() to accept and pass req to s3Service methods
Updated /api/deploy route to pass req object to deployService
Updated /api/artifacts/files route to pass req object to s3Service
Deployment now correctly uses custom build bucket when selected
NOTE: Frontend was not sending headers - fixed in v1.16.3
Fixed critical bug: S3Service now properly uses custom buckets from session
Updated listBuildArtifacts() to accept req parameter and use getBuckets()
Updated /api/check-access to use dynamic bucket selection
Updated /api/artifacts to pass req object to s3Service
Custom bucket selection now works correctly
Enhanced bucket selector with dropdown list of all available S3 buckets
Added GET /api/list-buckets endpoint to retrieve all S3 buckets
Replaced manual text input with searchable dropdown selector
Added bucket filter input for quick search through bucket list
Buckets are sorted alphabetically in dropdown
Default buckets marked with (default) label in dropdown
Shows total bucket count and creation dates
Improved UX: users can now select from existing buckets instead of typing names
Filter updates dropdown in real-time as user types
Added dynamic S3 bucket selector functionality
Users can now change Build Artifacts and Deploy WebUI buckets on-the-fly
Added bucket edit buttons on main page bucket status cards
Created bucket selector modal with validation and default bucket info
Implemented bucketOverride middleware for request-level bucket override
Added getBuckets() helper function in AWS config
Custom buckets stored in sessionStorage (temporary, resets on page refresh)
Updated frontend to send X-Custom-Build-Bucket and X-Custom-Deploy-Bucket headers
Bucket changes apply immediately with automatic page reload
Default buckets: jenkins-build-artfs (build), deploy-webui-bucket (deploy)
Fixed category display for all 9 game categories in main view
Updated versions.html to support resources, dashboard, event, jump-page, game-demo, ex-mgmt categories
Implemented prefix matching for event category (event-b, event-k auto-classified as Event)
Updated app.js getCategoryIcon() and getCategoryColor() with all 9 categories
Updated categoryOrder in renderCategoryView() and renderCardView()
Added custom CSS badge colors: bg-purple, bg-teal, bg-indigo
Jump Page and Game Demo now properly show item counts in UI
Enhanced game categorization system with complete category support
Added 6 new game categories:
- Resources: i18n, bundle-i18n, bundle-common, game-webview, bundle-common-freeBonus, game-configs
- Dashboard: gemini-dashboard
- Event: event
- Jump Page: jump-page
- Game Demo: GameDemo
- External Management: ex-mgmt
Updated categorizeArtifacts to support all new categories
All game artifacts now properly categorized based on release notes
Fixed deployment recording to show operations in Deployment History
Versions page deployments now appear in Deployment History
Added versionManager.recordDeployment() call in deployment API
Phase 1-3 Complete Optimization Release
Phase 1: Quick Improvements
- Added toast notification system for modern user feedback (success/error/warning/info)
- Implemented global search and filter system with real-time fuzzy matching
- Added category filters (Hash/Bingo/Arcade/All) for quick game filtering
- Implemented favorites system with localStorage persistence
- Added deployment presets management (save/load/delete)
- Built-in presets: All Hash Games, All Bingo Games, All Arcade Games
- Keyboard shortcuts: Ctrl+K (search), Ctrl+S (save preset), Ctrl+L (load preset)
- Search highlights matching text with yellow background
- Toast notifications auto-dismiss and stack properly (max 5)
Phase 2: Visual Enhancements
- Created comprehensive Dashboard with Chart.js statistics
- Added deployment trend charts (line chart for daily trends)
- Added success/failure distribution doughnut chart
- Added top 10 deployed games bar chart
- Implemented card view mode for artifacts browser
- Enhanced progress visualization with circular SVG progress rings
- Added stage tracking (Download → Extract → Upload → Verify → Complete)
- Improved visual feedback with color-coded progress states
- Dashboard auto-refreshes every 30 seconds
Phase 3: Advanced Features
- Parallel deployment already implemented with p-limit concurrency control
- Configurable parallelism via MAX_PARALLEL_ARTIFACTS env variable
- Added version comparison feature for side-by-side file analysis
- Version compare shows Added/Removed/Modified/Unchanged files
- File-level diff view with size comparison
- API endpoint for artifact file list extraction from ZIP files
Enhanced rollback functionality with real-time progress tracking
Renamed 'Redeploy' button to 'RollBack' for clarity
Added rollback progress modal with Socket.IO real-time updates
Integrated comprehensive audit logging for rollback operations
Audit logs record user, timestamp, artifacts, options, and duration
Rollback operations logged to logs/audit.log with full traceability
CSP-compliant event handling (removed inline onclick handlers)
Progress tracking shows artifact-level status during rollback
Added deployment history page with rollback functionality
View last 30 deployments with details (artifacts, files, status)
Redeploy button to rollback to previous deployments
Details modal shows artifact list and deployment options
New API endpoint: GET /api/deployment-history
Enhanced deployment records with artifactKeys and options
Added version comparison check before deployment
System now warns if artifact version is older than deployed version
Semantic version comparison (e.g., 1.0.5 < 1.0.6)
Warning dialog shows which artifacts are older with confirmation prompt
New API endpoint: POST /api/check-versions
Fixed game name parsing to extract full name before '-prd-'
Example: event-b-prd-1.0.6.zip now correctly deploys to event-b/
Pattern: {GameName}-prd-{version}.zip → {GameName}/
Supports game names with hyphens (e.g., event-b, multi-crash)
Removed auto-cleanup of source artifacts from jenkins-build-artfs
Build artifacts are now preserved after deployment
Only deploy-webui-bucket is cleared during deployment (if option enabled)
Fixed Game Versions page to display correct version number
Fixed authentication bypass issue
Moved route handlers before static file middleware
Now correctly redirects to login page when not authenticated
Security fix: index.html is now protected by authentication
Added custom prefix option for manual deployment path control
Empty prefix = Auto-parse game name from artifact filename
Custom prefix = Deploy all artifacts to specified directory
Flexible deployment strategy: auto or manual path selection
Clear operation respects custom prefix or auto-parsed game directories
Fixed progress percentage exceeding 100% (was showing 1000%+)
Fixed ZIP extraction to skip root directory
Now correctly deploys ZIP contents directly to game directory
Example: MultiPlayerCrashGR-prd-1.0.17.zip extracts to deploy-webui-bucket/MultiPlayerCrashGR/ (without intermediate directory)
Added progress clamping to all artifact and file progress calculations
Auto-parse game name from artifact filename
Example: MultiPlayerCrashNE-prd-1.0.20.zip → deploy-webui-bucket/MultiPlayerCrashNE/
Removed manual game name selector - fully automatic now
Each artifact deploys to its own game directory
Clear before deploy now clears only affected game directories
Deployment shows which games are being processed
Added game name selector for deployment (removed in 1.7.0)
10 predefined game names
Custom path option
Deploy button requires game name selection
Clear bucket clears selected game's directory
Auto-cleanup deployed artifacts from build bucket
Successfully deployed artifacts are automatically deleted from jenkins-build-artfs
Cleanup phase added to deployment process (95% progress)
Deployment log now includes cleaned artifacts count and size
Fixed progress percentage exceeding 100%
Added clamping to ensure progress stays within 0-100% range
Major improvement: Parallel artifact progress display
Now shows 3 separate progress cards for concurrent artifacts
Each card displays artifact name, status, progress bar, and current file
Visual indicators for downloading, extracting, and uploading states
Beautiful card-based UI with real-time progress updates
Enhanced deployment progress display
Now shows all files being uploaded simultaneously
Real-time progress tracking for concurrent uploads
Improved visual feedback during parallel deployment
Fixed delete validation regex bug (double backslash issue)
Delete functionality now works correctly for all file names
Optimized deployment speed with parallel artifact processing
Increased upload concurrency from 10 to 20
Added parallel artifact processing (up to 3 concurrent)
Significantly improved deployment performance for multiple artifacts
Added delete functionality for build artifacts
Delete button in Build Artifacts Browser
Support for deleting both files and directories
Confirmation dialog before deletion
Shows deleted items count and total size
Added version display on login page
Fixed AWS S3 region configuration (ap-east-1)
Updated build artifacts bucket to jenkins-build-artfs
Added Google OAuth2 authentication
Added email domain filtering (jvd.tw)
Configured proper S3 bucket access
Added real-time deployment progress with Socket.IO
Added progress percentage and current file display
Added game versions page to view version.txt from deployed games
Sorted Build Artifacts Browser by newest first
Improved deployment progress tracking
Initial release
S3 artifacts browser with subdirectory selection
Multi-select and select-all functionality
Deployment with delete-before-upload strategy
Automatic zip extraction during upload
Version management system
IAM policy with least privilege principle
